data.title: Bank takeover of Icelandic likely
data.meta_description: A subsidiary of Icelandic bank Landsbankinn is in the process of taking over Reykjavik-based seafood giant Icelandic Group.
data.meta_site_name: IntraFish.com | Latest seafood, aquaculture and fisheries news
data.text:
Vestia, a Landsbankinn subsidiary, is looking to acquire Icelandic Group in its entirety, according to Icelandic Group Chief Financial Officer Finnbogi Gylfason.

“It’s in the works,” Gylfason told IntraFish.

The deal has not yet happened, nor has any announcement been made by any of the parties, Gylfason said.

The ownership structure of the company remains in place, and there is no set timeline on when the deal might be completed, Gylfason said.

Executives from Vestia and Landsbankinn declined to comment.

After a string of acquisitions, Icelandic Group has struggled under the burden of high debt in recent years.
